column5: With cabin fever peaking,  I just want to Thank this board for existing.  Been awhile I've said thanks.  Thanks.   Grant

<object width="425" height="355"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DDg7kWgs5e0&hl=en"></param><param'>http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DDg7kWgs5e0&hl=en"></param><param name="wmode" value="transparent"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DDg7kWgs5e0&hl=en" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" wmode="transparent" width="425" height="355"></embed></object>

I would also like to extend my thanks to the board  I've only been here for a month or so but have already had the opportunity and privilage to participate in Fishin for Tyler, talk with OFNers and heed their advice to make educated purchases on fishing equipment and provide advice and opinions to other members where able.  I can only imagine the contributions of members and mods from years past.  Thank you for providing a great service, we are all in your debt.  reefrunner

That was great.  The walrus has trained her well!  It's been awhile since I brown-nosed the powers that be around here.  Do I get a fish?   P.s. Gerritt I've been meaning to drop you a pm about your work. Uh, guess i will.

Teacher, mother... secret lover..  I've been pro OFC ever since that faithful day I posted my first thread.  IF I were a vegetable and had to surf the web with a pen wedged in between my lips, I'd only need one default page...  Thanx everyone. merci, mille fois, merci.  HD

I would concur with that sentiment.  In the 4-5 yrs that i've participated here ( in a low- key way), met some good people, gained some computer savvy and learned a little more about  fishing and life.  Thanks,  ehg
I has a bukket?  Best to Snag and all the other walruses out there.
I concur! Thanks to the board and to all good members (you know who you are) like Snag   ... as for the PITAs, take off eh?
AWWWWWWW,  Shucks,  Confident in my heterosexuality, I just want to say I love you all.  I love GCD more when he's clothed.

Yep...this site has given me hours and hours of entertainment over the past year and a bit.  New friends have been made, lots of tips have been learned.  The people make this site work....so kudos to everyone...the mods, the members etc!!!

Thank you SNAG....If i recall last year around this time you started a snowball affect with the TO Island Pike. Those posts were great motivation to get off my azz and get out on the water...I guess the weather really hasn't been in your favour this year , but more reason to take up steelheading..... carefull though, its more of a disease than a hobby!!
